article.headline: Delaware State 66, Jacksonville St. 64
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Terrance Hunter scored 19 points, including a rebound basket at the buzzer, and Delaware State beat Jacksonville State 66-64 on Monday night. The game-winning shot was Hunter's seventh rebound. He grabbed the miss of Darrin Shine's jumper from 18 feet with 3 seconds left. Hunter made two free throws with 25 seconds left to give Delaware State a 64-63 lead, its first since 4-2. Walker Russell of Jacksonville State made one of two free throws with 24 seconds left for the game's final tie. Aaron Williams scored 15 points for the Hornets. B.J. Spencer lead Jacksonville State (4-6) with 19 points.
